{
  "name": "Ghost Sight",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "modules/pf1spheres/assets/icons/spheres/divination.webp",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You may spend a spell point to gain a sense that adds your caster level to Perception checks made to notice invisible or ethereal creatures. If you succeed at this check, the creature&#8217;s outline becomes visible to you. This negates both the usual penalties you would suffer attacking an invisible creature, and the bonuses the creature would normally gain against you. This continues until you lose line of sight to the creature, in which case you must succeed at a new Perception check to see them.</p>\n",
